&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kick start your career in the pharmacy department at University Hospitals of Leicester. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be given the opportunity to develop your skills to their full potential whilst working towards a level 3 QCF in armacy Service Skills and BTEC in Principles and Practice for Pharmacy Technicians. You will be provided with the training and support you need to become a registered Pharmacy Technician with the GPhC.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to be committed to learning and be highly motivated.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;On completion of the apprenticeship, you will be qualified to apply for Band 4 Pharmacy Technician roles within pharmacy eg Dispensary, Medicine Management, Clinical Trials, Aseptics etc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Minimum entry requirements are 5 GCSE’s at grade 4 or above or equivalent including Maths, English and Science&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There will be an expectation to work across the three sites of The University hospitals of Leicester and attend one day of college to complete the qualification, you will be part of the pharmacy team providing a quality service to patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taazeen Noray&lt;/strong&gt; - Specialist Pharmacy Technician - Training/MMT&lt;/p&gt;
